## Implementation

### Changes Made
- Created `src/burnt/advisor/__init__.py` - exports and module initialization
- Created `src/burnt/advisor/report.py` - `ComputeScenario` and `AdvisoryReport` models with display rendering
  - `display()` method detects Databricks notebook vs CLI, uses displayHTML() or rich tables
  - `comparison_table()` generates ASCII table matching DESIGN.md Compute Migration Analysis format
  - `what_if()` stub raises NotImplementedError pointing to Sprint 2 WhatIfBuilder
- Created `src/burnt/advisor/session.py` - `advise_current_session()` and `advise()` implementations
  - Uses real backend calls via `auto_backend()` detection
  - `advise_current_session()`: Gets metrics from backend, calculates baseline, projects scenarios, right-sizes cluster
  - `advise(run_id=...)`: Fetches from `system.query.history`, same projection logic
  - `advise(job_id=...)`: NotImplementedError stub for future enhancement
- Updated `src/burnt/__init__.py` - replaced stub with real implementation, added `advise()` function, added `right_size()` export
- Updated `src/burnt/cli/main.py` - enhanced advise command with `--run-id`, `--statement-id`, `--self`, `--output json/text`
- Created `tests/unit/test_advisor.py` - 13 tests covering models, session advisor, error messages, CLI integration
- Updated `tests/unit/test_api.py` - fixed test expectation from NotImplementedError to RuntimeError

### Implementation Notes
- Used real backend calls instead of mocks since `s1-01-runtime-backend` and `s1-02-instance-catalog` are already implemented
- Followed existing patterns for error handling and CLI integration
- Display implementation detects Databricks notebook environment via environment variables and dbutils
- Graceful degradation: clear error messages for missing Databricks context, missing credentials
- Job ID analysis stub raises NotImplementedError with helpful message about future release

